						               													<description>Reign of Dice is played in the form of a team match.&amp;#10;4 or 6 players are the best.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each team chooses one of the two camps. &amp;#10;We select and control one of the heroes of each camp. &amp;#10;There are 10 types more scenarios.&amp;#10;Depending on the scenario, you can play to free for all.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Select scenarios, camps and heroes. &amp;#10;Each player receives 15 cards from the deck, of which five start-up hands are selected, and the rest are returned to the deck.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each team takes turns. &amp;#10;One round is ended when all players play one turn.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each player's turn consists of four steps.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     Pulling out cards: Draw two cards from deck.&amp;#10;     Face 1: Choose whether to roll the dice. If you roll, must be as moved as the scale shown. If there is an enemy hero in the arrival compartment, take care of him immediately.&amp;#10;     Phase 2: Perform any of the following actions in the order you want them to:&amp;#10;         Use cards (However, multiple cards of the same color (type) cannot be used.)&amp;#10;         Use of hero capabilities (per hero, time and conditions of use vary and should be used accordingly.)&amp;#10;         Store use (the same store card cannot be used as a duplicate)&amp;#10;    &amp;#10;     Card Cleanup: If there are more than five pages of the handle, select and discard only five cards.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Winning conditions according to the scenario or&amp;#10;teams closer to winning conditions will win after the set round is over.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the designer&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
